The paper deals with the problem of patrolling a region with a set of mobile robots, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). The use of lid covers and the concept of minimum lid length suggest a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The optimization of the strategy for minimizing idle time involves algorithmic techniques and decision-making, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and swarm intelligence (cs.SI).
